The Federal Inland Revenue Service has issued a strong notice to all Ministries, Departments and Agencies (MDAs) of the Federal, State and Local Governments on outstanding tax payment, asking them to within 60 days remit all outstanding tax liabilities to the Service or will be compelled to do so through deduction from the budgetary allocation of the defaulting MDAs. The Service also stated that penalties and interests on outstanding taxes shall be recovered along with the principal tax liabilities. Full details of the notice can be found below: 